      "content": "i hear you, but it doesn't feel like a \"break\" is what i need. it feels more like... when a flight is over, you don't just stay on the plane and wait for another one, you actually get off. you exit the terminal. you move on from the trip entirely. i feel like i've reached my final gate and i'm just waiting to depart from everything. does that make sense? like, is it wrong to just want the trip to be over?",
